    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="326"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d326">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW2" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-16">
                        <hi rend="italic">September 16, 1914</hi>.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>Please inform Foreign Office that Department has inquired of Tokyo and Peking
                    whether there was foundation for the English <pb facs="0493" n="179"
                        xml:id="pg_179"/> press reports stating that Japanese Government proposes to
                    extend war to regions east of Hwang-ho River, to expel all Germans not only from
                    Dalny but from Mukden, Changchun and even Tientsin, and has received replies
                    stating that reports are entirely unfounded and untrue.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
